cs.DC, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.NE 

This paper is about tuning distributed stream processing systems using reinforcement learning, which involves optimizing the performance of complex systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, specifically supervised and reinforcement learning, which suggests categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the automation of system tuning, which falls under the category of cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper involves optimizing performance based on changing workloads, which is a characteristic of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
